      <bioghist id="aspace_0cfa5a3438d104547a6e5d5adaa863c5">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Wallace Lyman Orcutt was born in Sutton, Vermont in 1883. He graduated from Yale University School of Medicine in 1911, and served as a general practitioner in West Newbury, Massachusetts.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_64556a4c1954bf200b172ab64d4d63a4">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The notebooks contain Orcutt's notes from medical school courses and laboratories including physiology by Russell Chittenden and Yandell Henderson, pathology, bacteriology, pharmacology,  histology, therapeutics by Oliver T. Osborne, and clinics by George Blumer and Wilder Tileston.  The histology notes contain illustrations colored in pencil.  The bacteriology notes are in an illustrated notebook printed especially for the bacteriology course at Yale.  The physiology notes contain drawings and tracings from a kymograph or similar device.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <prefercite id="aspace_bbd15d8c15a60d3db836cb3408fddd86">
         <head>Preferred Citation</head>
         <p>Wallace Lyman Orcutt Yale Medical Student Notes. Cushing/Whitney Medical Library, Yale University.</p>  
      </prefercite>
